'''Alma mater''' is derived from the Latin term for "nourishing mother."  It is frequently used in the [[English language]] in reference to the [[university]] or [[college]] a person has attended.  In [[American English]], it is also in reference to a [[high school]] or [[elementary school]].  Alma mater is also sometimes used in reference to a school's anthem or song.  The word "matriculation" is derived from the Latin root word "mater."  The term suggests that the students are fed knowledge and taken care of by the university.

